    "body": "## Summary\n- skip benchmark-oriented test cases by default behind a new `perf` marker and `--run-perf` opt-in\n- trim slow Python test matrices and tensor sizes in the biggest CI hotspots to reduce repeated compile and execution cost\n- remove duplicated slow coverage and fix standalone collection for the kernel cache test module\n\n## Testing\n- `./format.sh`\n- `python -m pytest -q testing/python/profiler/test_tilelang_profiler.py`\n- `python -m pytest -q testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_reduce.py`\n- `python -m pytest -q testing/python/math/test_math_fast_math.py testing/python/math/test_math_ieee_math.py`\n- `python -m pytest -q testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_cumsum.py`\n- `python -m pytest -q testing/python/jit/test_tilelang_jit_gemm_cython.py -k 'not do_bench' testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_eager_jit.py testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_ptr.py`\n- `python -m pytest -q testing/python/cache/test_tilelang_kernel_cache.py -k 'test_cache_miss_detection and tvm_ffi'`\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added pytest markers (perf, slow) and a --run-perf option to categorize and selectively run performance/long-running tests; non-perf tests are skipped by default when appropriate.\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Reduced test workloads and default sizes across multiple test suites for faster, smaller-scale CI runs.\n  * Adjusted test helpers to support smaller defaults and conditional execution.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Removed coverage for the InjectTmaBarrier transform.\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Updated tracked TVM submodule.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
